cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DL 

This paper discusses keyword extraction, which is a task commonly studied in natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel method for constructing a graph of text and scoring words based on their semantic connectivity, which involves machine learning techniques and could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper mentions the use of statistical filters to identify candidate keywords, which could be related to cs.DL (Deep Learning) techniques.
